This paper deals with the problem of collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of machine learning and information retrieval. The use of maximum entropy is a common technique in machine learning, particularly in the field of natural language processing, which falls under the category of cs.CL. However, since this paper focuses on collaborative filtering, which is more closely related to recommendation systems and data mining, it is more likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with the problem of sparse data, it may also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
